==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Armiger
<hw>Ar"mi*ger</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>armiger</ets> armor bearer; <ets>arma</ets> arms +
<ets>gerere</ets> to bear.]</ety> <def>Formerly, an armor bearer, as of
a knight, an esquire who bore his shield and rendered other services. In
later use, one next in degree to a knight, and entitled to armorial
bearings. The term is now superseded by <xex>esquire</xex>.</def>
<rj><au>Jacob.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Armigerous</ent>⟦br⟧
